					<div class="commentbody">I have to disagree with your assertion that using a water bath to bake this cake would somehow make it something other than new your style. New York style refers to the INGREDIENTS. Not to baking it without a water bath. Indeed, the waterbath convention was adopted to prevent cracks. What makes a cheese cake new york style is that it "relies upon heavy cream, cream cheese, eggs and egg yolks to add a richness and a smooth consistency." So there. :P</div>
