					<div class="commentheading">On November 13, 2008 at 10:23 AM, Stephie (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>How do I get the bottom off without destroying the cake</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I had the same problem and found that if you line the bottom of the spring form pan with greaseproof paper it helps. When the cake is cooled or has been set in the fridge overnight you need two wide flat plates the second should be the one you intend to serve it on. You can then use the first plate to invert it onto so the the bottom is on top, do this gently so you don't crack your cake top. Remove the bottom of the pan and invert it again onto your serving plate. Hope this helps</div>
