					<div class="commentheading">On November 15, 2008 at 08:15 PM, Sonja (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>French substitute for Philly cream cheese</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">In France, the nearest you can get to Philadelphia cream cheese is 'St Moret' (Fromage nature) - available at Carrefour supermarkets. The next best is 'Carre Frais' by 'Elle &amp; Vivre' (Fromage Frais) available at Champion, and then as a last resort, you can use 'Kiri' (Fromage Blanc Fondu) available at Lidl supermarkets.  The best is St Moret - I lived in Germany for 5 years, and it's found on the shelf next to 'Philadelphia' - I can't tell the difference between the two. :)</div>
