					<div class="commentheading">On October 19, 2009 at 10:55 PM, an anonymous reader said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject">Subject: <span>Very very dark top</span><br /></div>
					<div class="commentbody">After 10 min at 500 deg, the top was *very* dark, almost burnt.  I opened the oven and fanned the door to drop the temp faster because I was afraid it would burn.  Also, I took the temp first at 1 hr 30 min, and it was already over 160.  Might be the oven needs calibrating.  No cracks though.<br />
I finished with a fig sauce.  I warmed up a small jar of fig preserves and strained the chunks out, then added some gelatin to the syrup that was left.  I poured it over the top of the cake while it was still in the springform and let it chill and set up.<br />
It was a big hit.<br />
