					<div class="commentheading">On November 27, 2010 at 05:35 PM, Dilbert said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">a seven inch diameter would be closer to "half" the volume - so the eight inch will be a bit thinner / not as 'deep' - <br />
<br />
if you go with 8" you'll need more than half the crust - 10" is 78+ sq inches, 8" 50 sq inches.<br />
<br />
also be aware it will bake faster - so keep an eye on on it - do not go blindly by a timer.<br />
<br />
the black non-stick pans will handle any temp your oven can generate (well, except for the self-cleaning cycle, if you've got that...)</div>
